IPInfusionsBGPHighAvailabilitybasedonstatefulswitchover(SSO)providesasolutionwhichallows

BGPHighAvailabilityusingSSOallowsBGPtocontinuefunctioningandnon-stopforwardingofdata

Intheabovediagram,routerR7playstheroleofstandbyrouter.BGPrunsinthisrouterinhotstandy
mode,meaningallthestatesanddataoftheBGPfromtheactiverouterR1iscontinuouslygetting

WhenasoftwareorahardwarefailureisdetectedatR1,anodeswitchoveristriggred,whichcausesR7

SohowdoesIPInfusionssolutionmaintaintheBGPadjacencieswhileswitchingovertoaredundant
node?
ConsidertheBGProutingprotocolisdeployedina1:1redundancymode.Bothactiveandstandby
nodesrunBGPinstance,however,theBGPinstanceonthestandbyrunsindormantmode,i.e.it
neithersendsoutnorprocessesanycontrolpacketbutkeepsitsstatesanddatafullysynchronized
withthatofActiveBGP.
ActiveBGPformsadjacencywithaneighboringBGPusingTCPconnection.Allneighborinformationis
synchronizedwithstandbyaswell.IfthestandbyhastoreplicatetheTCPconnectionalso,itneedsto
createtheTCPsocketendpoint,binditwithsameIPaddressandportnumberasthatoftheActiveBGP
andsendaTCPconnectionrequesttoNeighbor-BGP.ButtheTCPstackontheneighborBGPwillnot
allowthisconnectionsincethelocalendpointisalreadyinusebytheActive-BGP.Asaresult,an
adjacencycanexistsonlybetweentheActive-BGPandtheNeighbor-BGP.
IfafaultoccursontheActive-BGP,theStandby-BGPhastotakeovertheroleoftheactive.AllTCP
sessionsestablishedbetweenActive-BGPandNeighbor-BGPneedstobemigratedtoStandby-BGP
(whichisnewactive)andNeighbor-BGPwithouttheknowledgeoftheNeighbor-BGP.Butthereisone
problemhere.ThemomentActive-BGPdiesduestoanyfault,itsTCPStackimmediatelysendsaFIN
packettotheneighborTCPstack.AsaresulttheTCPstackoftheNeighbor-BGPnodealreadyknows
thatActive-BGPhasclosedtheconnection,evenbeforetheswitchovercanhappen.Anyattemptto
restoretheTCPsessionbetweenStandby-BGP(whichisnewactive)andtheNeighbor-BGPresultsinto
Neighbor-BGPsendingaTCPRSTpackettotheStandby-BGPandhenceadjacenciesdoesnotgets
formedaftertheswitchover.TheonlyoptionlefthereistocreatenewTCPconnectionsbetweenthe
Standby-BGP(whichisnewactive)andalltheneighbors.ButthiswillbeagainsttheprincipleofSSO
whichassumesthattheswitchover/failoveriscompletelytransparenttotheneighbors.
Thesolutiontothisproblemliesintheabilityofcreatingapassive-TCPsessionbetweentheStandby-
BGPandtheNeighbor-BGPwheneveranActive-BGPestablishesanadjacencywithaNeighbor-BGP.
Thetermpassive-TCPsessionhasbeenusedinthisdocumenttodescribeaTCPsessionwhichis
establishedwithoutexchanginganyTCPpacketbetweentwoendpoints.ThuswhenanActive-BGP
formsanadjacencywithaNeighbor-BGP,theStandby-BGPcreatesapassive-BGPsessionwiththe
sameneighborwithoutanyknowledgeofthe
Neighbor-BGP.WhentheActive-BGPdies,thefollowingaredone
Active-BGPispreventedfromsendingtheFINpackettotheNeighbor-BGP
Standby-BGPtakestheroleoftheactiveandallthepassiveBGPsessionsareturnedintoactive(TCP
packetsstartsflowingonthissessions).
TotheNeighbor-BGP,itappearsthatitsTCPsessionwithActive-BGPneverwentdownandthusBGP
keepsoperatingnormallyandNonStopRouting(NSR)isachieved.
ThesolutiondescribedaboverequireschangesintheTCPstackitselftosupportthecreationofpassive
TCPsession.ThiscapabilityhasbeenalreadyaddedinLinuxKernel3.5onwards.Anewsocketmode
TCP_REPAIRhasbeenaddedintheTCPstackwhichallowscreationofapassiveTCPconnection.
Forexample,itispossibletocreateasocketandputitintorepairmode.Onceasocketisinrepair
mode,anyoperationperformedonthissocketmovestheTCPstateappropriatelywithoutexchanging
anypacketwiththeremoteTCP.Forexample,callingconnectwithasocketinrepairmodewould
movetheTCPstatemachinetoEstablishedstatebutthethree-wayhandshakewiththeremote
TCPwillnothappen.
IPInfusionsBGPHighAvailabilitySolutionmakesuseofTCP_REPAIRoptiontoprovidethe
checkpointingandrestoreofBGPsessionsalongwithprotocolsstateanddata.Thus,itallowsBGPto
performanStatefulSwitchoverinatruesensewithoutaffectingthedataforwardingandrouting
functionswhileSSOtakesplacewhichishighlydesirableinBGPdeployments.
